In this example, the `\tableofcontents` command is placed right after the `\maketitle` command in the preamble, which is not recommended because it will generate the ToC before the document content. Instead, you should use the `\frontmatter` command before the ToC to indicate that it belongs to the preamble, and the `\mainmatter` command before the first section of the document content. This way, the ToC will be generated automatically and updated whenever you add, remove, or modify sections in the document.

Additionally, you can use the `\tableofcontents*` command instead of `\tableofcontents` to suppress the automatic page numbering of the ToC. This can be useful if you want to include the ToC in the table of contents itself or if you want to create a list of figures or tables with the same format as the ToC. For example:

```latex
